<%# Sourced vs Influenced pipeline by channel for a typical B2B SaaS team. Illustrative numbers. %>

<%
  channels = [
    { name: "LinkedIn Ads",    sourced: 180_000, influenced: 720_000 },
    { name: "Content / SEO",   sourced: 240_000, influenced: 980_000 },
    { name: "Webinars",        sourced: 120_000, influenced: 540_000 },
    { name: "Events",          sourced: 60_000,  influenced: 320_000 },
    { name: "Email nurture",   sourced: 30_000,  influenced: 410_000 },
    { name: "Partner referral",sourced: 90_000,  influenced: 220_000 }
  ]
  scale = channels.map { |c| c[:influenced] }.max
%>

<figure class="my-12 not-prose">
  <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">

    <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 pt-8 pb-6 border-b border-slate-200">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 tracking-tight">Sourced vs Influenced pipeline by channel</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm sm:text-base mt-1">In B2B, the channel that <em>sources</em> a deal is rarely the one doing the most influence work.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="px-4 sm:px-8 py-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-50/60 to-white">

      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-5 gap-y-1.5 mb-5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide text-slate-600">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-slate-400"></span>
          Sourced (first-touch)
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-indigo-500"></span>
          Influenced (any-touch in journey)
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <% channels.each do |c| %>
          <% sourced_pct = (c[:sourced].to_f / scale * 100).round %>
          <% influenced_pct = (c[:influenced].to_f / scale * 100).round %>
          <% ratio = (c[:influenced].to_f / c[:sourced]).round(1) %>
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-2">
              <h3 class="text-sm sm:text-base font-bold text-slate-900"><%= c[:name] %></h3>
              <div class="text-xs font-mono text-indigo-700 font-semibold"><%= ratio %>&times; ratio</div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-1.5">
              <div class="w-14 sm:w-20 text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-wider text-slate-500 shrink-0">SOURCED</div>
              <div class="flex-1 h-5 sm:h-6 bg-slate-100 rounded-sm overflow-hidden">
                <div class="h-full bg-slate-400 rounded-sm" style="width: <%= sourced_pct %>%;"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="w-16 sm:w-20 text-right text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono font-semibold text-slate-700 shrink-0">$<%= (c[:sourced] / 1000).to_s.reverse.scan(/\d{1,3}/).join(",").reverse %>k</div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="w-14 sm:w-20 text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-bold tracking-wider text-indigo-600 shrink-0">INFL.</div>
              <div class="flex-1 h-5 sm:h-6 bg-indigo-50 rounded-sm overflow-hidden">
                <div class="h-full bg-indigo-500 rounded-sm" style="width: <%= influenced_pct %>%;"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="w-16 sm:w-20 text-right text-xs sm:text-sm font-mono font-semibold text-indigo-700 shrink-0">$<%= (c[:influenced] / 1000).to_s.reverse.scan(/\d{1,3}/).join(",").reverse %>k</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 py-5 bg-slate-50 border-t border-slate-200">
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-slate-900">Influenced pipeline is typically 3&ndash;5&times; sourced.</strong>
        Email and webinars rarely <em>source</em> deals (people don't usually first hear about you in their inbox), but they touch most opportunities along the way. Cutting "low-sourcing" channels usually hurts deals already in motion.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
  <figcaption class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-3 text-center">
    Illustrative pipeline values for a $5&ndash;15M ARR B2B SaaS &middot; Pattern (3&ndash;5&times; influenced/sourced ratio) holds across most B2B benchmarks
  </figcaption>
</figure>
